track_notes:
This is a challenging round of 13.3 M/21.3 KM with 4700 ft / 1433m ascent from Seathwaite car park area NY 236123 going over Seathwaite Fell, Great End, Scafell Pike, Allen Crags, Glaramara and Rosthwaite Fell (Bessyboot) back to Seathwaite. I completed the route in around 10 hours on a clear day in March 2011 although it was dark when we finished at 7.30pm having set out at 9.20am.
For more detailed info see wainwrightsontheair.blogspot.co.uk
track_title: LD-001 Scafell Pike - long WOTA round with five extra Wainwrights

track_notes: Walked in September 2015. Seathwaite > Styhead > Lingmell Col > Scafell Pike > Great End (WOTA LDW-005) > Allen Crags (WOTA LDW-042)> Styhead > Seathwaite
track_title: Corridor Route from Seathwaite includes 2 extra Wainwrights
